{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Create powers to increase sentences where a defendant refuses to attend court",
        "additional_details": "By refusing to attend court defendants are refusing to face the consequences of their actions. We believe this is an insult to the court and victims.\r\n \r\nIf a defendant refuses to attend court then judges should have the power to add a penalty term for non-appearance of up to 5 years dependant on the offence.\r\n",
        "background": "Where a defendant is in custody but refuses to attend court, we want the courts to be given powers to increase any sentence applied.",
